  "title": "Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>About Us</strong></u></p><p>We are a Chartered Accounting Firm established since 1973 and have a very good client base. Our clients are from a wide range of industries, from manufacturers, diamond and jewelry wholesalers, shipping, merchants, investment holding companies, biotech companies, oil and bio fuel, coffee bean suppliers, chains of restaurants and cafes, finance companies and fund managers, IT hardware and software, construction and engineering, paper processing companies etc. both local and international. We also provide financial due diligence services in addition to audits.</p><p><u><strong>Job Summary</strong></u></p><p>Provide administrative and secretarial support to the audit team while coordinating client communications and managing document control to ensure smooth audit operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide secretarial support to the audit team by preparing and organizing documents to facilitate audit processes</li><li>Communicate with clients to collect and clarify information for their management accounts</li><li>Manage document control by organizing, filing, and maintaining audit-related records accurately</li><li>Coordinate courier services to ensure timely delivery and receipt of audit documents</li><li>Perform additional administrative duties as assigned by management to support team efficiency</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficient in spoken and written English to communicate effectively with clients and team members</li><li>Skilled in using Microsoft Word, Excel, and PDF software to prepare and manage audit documents</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>At least 1 year of experience working in an accounting office environment to handle audit-related administrative tasks efficiently</li><li>Demonstrate a pleasant and cheerful disposition with strong interpersonal skills to foster positive client and team interactions</li></ul>",
